text: Limerick () is a city and the county seat of County Limerick in the historical province of Munster, in the midwest of Ireland. The city lies on the River Shannon, with three main crossing points near the city centre. In 2022 there were 205,444 people living in the city. More than 34,000 were students and half the population were under 35. == References == == Other websites == * * Limerick City Council * LimerickPride * Architecture of Limerick * Various online history resources from Limerick City Library Category:County towns in Ireland Category:9th-century establishments in Europe Category:Establishments in the Republic of Ireland
